&lt;p&gt;A combination, not necessarily all-inclusive, of the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute reproducible experiments on our large data catalog to further the understanding of model performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and evaluate novel CVML techniques, ranging from CNNs to large Transformer-based Foundation models, to improve our products.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute and improve existing rigorous model evaluation pipelines.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate on debugging and troubleshooting issues in ML models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lean into the responsible use of AI for software development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience and Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Data Science, Statistics, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-2 years of relevant engineering work experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the fundamentals of statistical learning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with the Python data science and ML stack: PyTorch, NumPy, pandas, scikit-learn.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving and analytical skills with a keen attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work collaboratively in a team environment and effectively communicate complex technical concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for emerging technologies, artificial intelligence, and computer vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
